Name: corneal intraepithelial neoplasm
Definition: An arthritis that is an autoimmune disease which develops due to an infection located elsewhere in the body.

Name: in situ carcinoma
Definition: A carcinoma that is an early development defined by the absence of invasion of surrounding tissues.
Synonym: carcinoma in situ of respiratory tract (disorder)

Name: obsolete soft tissue disease
Definition: A carcinoma that is an early development defined by the absence of invasion of surrounding tissues.

Name: actinic keratosis
Definition: A monocytic leukemia where the majority of monocytic cells are promonocytes.
